: <span class=\"fn\">α</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Max.html#IsTop\">IsTop</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span> ∉ <span class=\"fn\">t</span></span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Let `s` be a dense set in a nontrivial dense linear order `α`. If `s` is a\nseparable space (e.g., if `α` has a second countable topology), then there exists a countable\ndense subset `t ⊆ s` such that `t` does not contain bottom/top elements of `α`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Order/DenselyOrdered.html#Dense.exists_countable_dense_subset_no_bot_top","kind":"theorem","line":253,"name":"Dense.exists_countable_dense_subset_no_bot_top","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Topology/Order/DenselyOrdered.lean#L253-L265"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Order/DenselyOrdered.html#DenselyOrdered.subsingleton_of_discreteTopology\"><span class=\"name\">DenselyOrdered</span>.<span class=\"name\">subsingleton_of_discreteTopology</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Defs/LinearOrder.html#LinearOrder\">LinearOrder</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/T